278
00:20:07,122 --> 00:20:11,122
Heidi, are you satisfied? Can you move something?

279
00:20:14,122 --> 00:20:17,122
But Miss Clara, should I push it for you?

280
00:20:19,122 --> 00:20:21,122
Yes, good.

281
00:20:25,618 --> 00:20:29,618
Would you like to go back to your mountains?

282
00:20:30,618 --> 00:20:33,618
Do you love the mountains so much?

283
00:20:34,618 --> 00:20:36,618
Oh, so you can't do anything about it.

284
00:20:36,618 --> 00:20:42,618
I thought we could be friends, Heidi, but you can't stand it here in Frankfurt.

285
00:20:43,618 --> 00:20:46,618
Should I tell Mr. Rottmeier to get your aunt?

286
00:20:46,618 --> 00:20:48,618
Yes, please do that.

287
00:20:48,618 --> 00:20:52,412
I think it's a shame. I like you. It would have been very funny...

288
00:20:52,412 --> 00:20:55,412
...if I hadn't been able to get along with the two of us.

289
00:20:55,412 --> 00:20:58,412
I like you too, but I think, you know...

290
00:20:58,412 --> 00:21:00,412
Then I'm alone again.

291
